{"cursor":"23095","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox scientist |name = Nicholas A. Christakis |image = Nicholas\nChristakis.jpg |image_size = |caption =\n||birth_date =\n|birth_place = United States |residence = New Haven, Connecticut, United States\n|nationality = |death_date = |death_place = |field = Sociology; Biosocial\nScience, Medicine |work_institution = University of Pennsylvania University\nof Chicago Harvard Medical School Harvard University Yale University\n|alma_mater = Yale University Harvard University University of\nPennsylvania |doctoral_advisor = RenÃ©e Fox |doctoral_students = Marcus\nAlexander, Jonathan Beauchamp, Virginia W. Chang, Peter DeWan, Felix Elwert,\nDanielle Harvey, Jack Iwashyna, Lei Jin, David Kim, Sae Takada, Alison Hwong,\nMark Pachucki, Jessica Perkins, Ming Wen, Coren Apicella (postdoc), Sam Arbesman\n(postdoc), Jason Block (postdoc), Damon Centola (postdoc), Feng Fu (postdoc),\nElizabeth Lamont (postdoc), Jukka Pekka Onnela (postdoc), Niels Rosenquist (postdoc)[http://christakis.med.harvard.edu/pages/the-lab/subnav/students-\ncolleagues.html] |known_for = |prizes = |religion = |footnotes = }} 'Nicholas A.\nChristakis' (born May 7, 1962) is an American physician and social scientist\nknown for his research on social networks and on the socioeconomic and biosocial\ndeterminants of behavior, health, and longevity. As of July 2013, he is the Sol\nGoldman Family Professor of Social and Natural Science at Yale University. [http://news.yale.edu/2013/04/11/new-institute-will-advance-\ninterdisciplinary-study-networks Tom Conroy, \"New \"Institute Will Advance the\nInterdisciplinary Study of Networks,\" Yale News April 11, 2013.] He\ndirects the [http://www.humannaturelab.net Human Nature Lab], and he is the Co-\nDirector of the Yale Institute for Network Science. Until July 2013, he was a\nProfessor of Medical Sociology in the Department of Health Care Policy and a\nProfessor of Medicine in the Department of Medicine at Harvard Medical School; a\nProfessor of Sociology in the Department of Sociology in the Harvard Faculty of\nArts and Sciences; and an Attending Physician at the Harvard-affiliated Mt.\nAuburn Hospital. [http://www.edge.org/3rd_culture/bios/christakis.html Edge,\nThe Third\nCulture] [http://www.edge.org/3rd_culture/bios/christakis.html\nNicholas Christakis's Page at Harvard Medical School] From 2009 to 2013,\nChristakis and his wife, Erika Christakis, were Co-Masters of Pforzheimer House,\none of Harvard's twelve residential\nhouses. [http://www.thecrimson.com/article.aspx?ref=526535 Bita M. Asad and\nAhmed Mabruk, \"Christakises To Be Pfoho House Masters,\" The Harvard Crimson,\nFebruary 17, 2009.]\n\nChristakis is also known for his popular undergraduate lecture class \"Life and\nDeath in the USA\" which is\n[http://christakis.med.harvard.edu/pages/podcasts.html podcast publicly], and\nfor attracting a diverse group of faculty and students from across University\ndepartments and professional schools into his\n[http://christakis.med.harvard.edu/pages/research_group.html research group].\n\nIn 2009, he was named to the Time 100, Time magazine's list of the 100 most\ninfluential people in the world. [http://www.time.com/time/specials/package-\ns/article/0,28804,1894410_1893209_1893472,00.html Dan Ariely, \"Time 100,\" Time\nMagazine.] In 2009 and again in 2010, Christakis was named by Foreign\nPolicy magazine to its list of top global thinkers. [http://www.foreignpoli-\ncy.com/articles/2010/11/29/the_fp_top_100_global_thinkers?page=0,44 \"Foreign\nPolicy Magazine\"]\n\nHe was elected to the Institute of Medicine of the National Academy of Sciences\nin 2006, and he was named a Fellow at the American Association for the\nAdvancement of Science in 2010.\n\nChristakis is of Greek descent. http://www.ekathimerini.com/4dcgi/_w_articl-\nes_wsite4_1_22/05/2009_372658 \"The Greek-American scientist talked to\nKathimerini English Edition, explaining, among other things, why we shouldnât\nquite expect the ripple effect to reach our office cubicles.\"\n","linknr":361,"url":"Nicholas_A._Christakis","recorded":1374763380,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Nicholas_A._Christakis&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Nicholas_A._Christakis&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/File:Nicholas_Christakis.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/02/Nicholas_Christakis.jpg/220px-Nicholas_Christakis.jpg","/wiki/United_States","/wiki/New_Haven,_Connecticut","/wiki/United_States","/wiki/Sociology","/wiki/Sociobiology","/wiki/Medicine","/wiki/University_of_Pennsylvania","/wiki/University_of_Chicago","/wiki/Harvard_Medical_School","/wiki/Harvard_University","/wiki/Yale_University","/wiki/Alma_mater","/wiki/Yale_University","/wiki/Harvard_University","/wiki/University_of_Pennsylvania","/wiki/Doctoral_advisor","/wiki/Ren%C3%A9e_Fox","http://christakis.med.harvard.edu/pages/the-lab/subnav/students-colleagues.html","/wiki/Physician","/wiki/Social_scientist","#cite_note-1","http://www.humannaturelab.net","/wiki/Harvard_Medical_School","/wiki/Harvard_Faculty_of_Arts_and_Sciences","#cite_note-2","#cite_note-3","/wiki/Pforzheimer_House","/wiki/Harvard","/wiki/Harvard_College#